                    <ab>[In nomine sanct]e et individue trinitatis. <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/239">Otto</persName> divina favente clementia Romanorum <rs
                            key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> augustus. Si dignis nostr[oru]m
                        fidelium petitionibus adsensum prebuerimus, devotiores [eos esse in obsequio
                        nostri] famulatus [minime] diffidimus. [Q]uocirca omnium sanctae dei
                        e[c]cl[esiae] fidelium nostrorumque presentium scilic[et ac] futurorum
                        com[periat universitas, qualiter] interventu <rs key="#parentOf">nostrae
                            dominae [matri]s</rs>
                        <persName key="#Queen #parentOf" ref="#people/1301">Adheleide</persName>+
                            <rs key="#Queen">imperatricis</rs> semper augustae<orgName
                            key="#Collegiate_churches">
                            <rs key="#Collegiate_churches">sancte Mar[iae] canonicis
                                Ueronensibus</rs></orgName> preceptum confirmationis et
                        corrobor[ationi]s, quatinus nos pro d[ei] amore nostr[aeque] animae remedio
                        de quadam <rs
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >corte</rs> que+ nominatur <placeName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#places/966"><geogName
                                key="#Churches #Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#estates/564">Quinto</geogName></placeName> sita i[n <geogName
                            key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/514"><rs key="#Comitatus">comitatu</rs>
                            Montesirica]no</geogName>, quam quidam nomine <persName>Lanzo
                        </persName>pro remed[io] anim[ae] sue+ donavit prefatis Ueronen[sibus]
                        canonicis, cum <rs key="#Churches">capella</rs> et cu[m] omnibus eius
                        pertinentiis, alteram autem que+ vocatur <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/565"><rs
                                key=" #Churches #Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                    ><placeName
                                    key=" #Churches #Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                    ref="#places/967">[Titu]lus</placeName></rs></geogName>, ubi
                        dicitur <placeName ref="#places/968">Uilla</placeName>, cum <rs
                            key="#Churches">capella</rs> sua in [hono]re sancte+ [Ma]rie+
                        [con]s[tru]cta cum omnibus p[ertinentii]s [su]is quam obtulit
                                <persName><name ref="Angelbertus/Reginzo">Angel[b]ertu[s]
                            </name></persName><rs key="#Priests">clericus</rs> q[ui]
                        cognom[ina]b[at]ur [Reginzo], in eodem comitatu positam, [terciam vero que
                        nuncu]patur <placeName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ><geogName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#estates/566"><rs
                                    key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                    >Badabones</rs></geogName></placeName>, [quam] tribuit <persName
                            key="#Bishops" ref="#people/1200">Not[k]erius</persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">Ueronensis episcopus </rs>pater Ueronensium cleric[orum],
                        positam <geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/567">in Tridentino
                            comitatu</geogName> cum capella [et] om[nibus] pertinentiis et
                        adiacentiis eius, [insuper] <rs
                            key="#Casalia #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >cassales</rs> duos <geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/124">[in
                            Ueronen]si comitatu</geogName> [iacentes in corte regia que+] vocatur
                            <placeName
                            key="#Casalia #Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention"
                            ref="#places/4144"><geogName
                                key="#Casalia #Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention"
                                ref="#estates/1404"><rs
                                    key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention"
                                    >Zirpa</rs></geogName></placeName>, quos obtulit <persName><name
                                ref="Andreperga/Giza">An[dreperga] que+ [Giz]a</name></persName>
                        vocatur, cum omnibus <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terris</rs> [<rs
                            key="#Wine">vineis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Hay/fodder">pratis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Cereals">campi]s </rs>cultis et incultis <rs key="Mills"
                            >molendinis</rs> [seu] cum [omni]bus [rebus eorum] mobilibus et
                        immobilibus que+ dici aliquo modo vel nominari p[ossunt], concedere
                        dignaremur, eo [videlicet ordine ut], ubicumque a prenomin[at]is [canoni]cis
                        suo[rum]ve [successoribus] aliquando possess[um est] vel [in] f[uturo]
                        possessurum erit, omnium contra[dictio]ne et dimino[ra]tio[ne] violent[orum]
                        exclusa, firmiter proprietario detineant iure. H[oc etiam nostra imperiali
                        auctoritate] addimus [pro redemptione et rem]edio anime+ [nostri] patris
                        imperatoris <persName key="#Emperor/king #parentOf" ref="#people/173"
                            >Ottonis</persName> [et nostrae dominae] matris imperatricis Adeleide+
                        nec non [et] nostre+ et concedimus largimur donamus, [quo ho]mines [cuncti
                        permorantes atque residentes in castris ipsorum canonicorum, quorum <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >castrorum</rs> nomina haec sunt: <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle #Albergaria/gifori #Teloneum"
                            ref="#places/961"><geogName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle #Albergaria/gifori #Teloneum"
                                ref="#estates/557">Cerreta</geogName></placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle #Albergaria/gifori #Teloneum"
                            ref="#places/962"><geogName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle #Albergaria/gifori #Teloneum"
                                ref="#estates/558">Biunda</geogName></placeName>], <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle #Albergaria/gifori #Teloneum"
                            ref="#places/1804"><geogName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle #Albergaria/gifori #Teloneum"
                                ref="#estates/3019">Porcile</geogName></placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle #Albergaria/gifori #Teloneum"
                            ref="#places/963"><geogName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle #Albergaria/gifori #Teloneum"
                                ref="#estates/559">Pullianu[m]</geogName></placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle #Albergaria/gifori #Teloneum"
                            ref="#places/964"><geogName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle #Albergaria/gifori #Teloneum"
                                ref="#estates/560">Martiana</geogName></placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle #Albergaria/gifori #Teloneum"
                            ref="#places/965"><geogName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle #Albergaria/gifori #Teloneum"
                                ref="#estates/561">Gra[tian]a</geogName></placeName>, <placeName
                            ref="#places/577"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle #Albergaria/gifori #Teloneum"
                                ><geogName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle #Albergaria/gifori #Teloneum"
                                ref="#estates/562">Pruno</geogName></placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle #Albergaria/gifori #Teloneum"
                            ref="#places/4117"><geogName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle #Albergaria/gifori #Teloneum"
                                >C[astellione</geogName></placeName>, ut <rs
                            key="#Albergaria/gifori">fodrum</rs> quod iniu]ste [et] non leg[aliter
                        dederunt], quod nefas [nam] erat, preceptali pagina nostre+ auctoritatis
                        volu[mus ut] deinceps [non] dent, nec non et ipsi qui in civitate soliti
                        erant dare [<rs key="#Teloneum">thelon]eum</rs> [precipiendo iubemus]; nec
                        in tempore ullo a[liquis eis auferat vel de] hoc amplius molestare ipsos
                        temptet. Pre+cipi[en]tes denique [iuben]do sancimus ut nullus dux episcopus
                        [m]archio comes viceco[m]es nullaque [nostri regni m]agna vel parva persona
                        sancte+ Ueronensis ecclesie+ canonicos de omnibus prememoratis causis seu de
                        omnibus libellariis colonis ad sese p[ertinenti]bus aliisque in prediis
                        eorundem canonicor[um] ressid[entibus] molestare disvestire angariare vel
                        per placita fatigare nis[i] tantum ante [i]llorum p[resentiam audeat vel
                        pr]esumat. Contra quod nostr[ae confirmationis] siv[e] concessionis
                        preceptum si quis aliquando ins[u]rg[ere] t[em]pt[averi]t, sciat se
                        compositurum <rs key="#Penalty">auri purissimi libras [centum]</rs>,
                        med[ietatem] <rs key="#Camera_regis">kamere+ [nostrae] </rs>et medie[tatem]
                        canonicis ibidem [pro tempore deservientibus. Qu]od [ut verius credatur
                        diligentiusque] ab omnibus observetur, hanc paginam prop[ria] manu
                        corrobor[antes eam] inferius iussimus sigillare. Signum domni Ottonis
                        secundi serenissimi imperatoris (M.) e[t invict]issimi augusti. [<persName
                            key="#Chancellor"><name ref="Adelbertus">Adelbertus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs> ad]vicem <persName
                            key="#Archchancellor #Bishops"><name ref="Petrus"
                            >Petri</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Archchancellor #Bishops">episcopi et archicancellarii
                        </rs>reco[gnovi et] subscripsi. (SI. D.)</ab>
